Mafdet's Ledger Houses are the institutional heirs of the Eastern Desert's administrative tradition: the Littoral Branch of Measure Script, developed by Keeper-era coastal scribes, became the foundation of Mafdet's maritime contract notation. Shoreward Assessors — the specialist clerks who translated cargo from inland water-law assessment to maritime risk-assessment at the Shoreward Seal boundary — are the professional ancestors of Mafdet's current Ledger House clerks. Mafdet attests desert-origin cargo through the same three-route logic inherited from the Saltglass Reach: swift-line documentation for high-value goods, heavy-road assessment for bulk commodities, sealed-route requirements for pyramid-provenance and funerary consignments. The Jackal Synod's Eclipsed Tongues faction uses Glasswind routes through the Saltglass Reach to move relic materials toward Mafdet's harbor for maritime export, bypassing inland Synod-controlled inspection points — a smuggling pattern that Mafdet's Harbor Wardens track but have not fully suppressed. Desert salt ledger tablets, when they reach Mafdet's market, command premium prices from scholarly buyers because they document the transition from route commonwealth to necro-bureaucratic monarchy that underlies the entire regional legal tradition.

